VALLEY EARNINGS: MICROPOLIS REPORTS LOSS OF $24 MILLION IN 3RD QUARTER 
Micropolis Corp. announced that it lost about $24 million on sales of about $67 
million in the third quarter ended September 29, compared to a loss of $13 
million on sales of $95 million in the previous year. The Chatsworth maker of 
disk drives attributed the 30% drop in revenues to lower demand for some types 
of disk drives, which are data storage devices for computers. 
